Your document does not contain the forward references (??). Also in a document this short, there is no need for having multiple sections, or giving forward references at all. Nevertheless, the structure it provides is appreciated. 

Where did you find this definition of a CREW transaction? In the original work, it is basically about a key-value store, where certain key ranges are only modified by one node, but can be read by all. There is no notion of cross-object transactions.

From this, your argument for Claim 1 makes less sense, even though I still agree with the conclusion. Also, depending on the workload, one or the other might be better, or a combination of both. The combination of both is valid, though.

